topic.title: Can you reset/delete your user id?
topic.body: If you can, how? I've heard that resetting your userid once in a while was the only way to stay truly anonymous, even with tor.

1565237461_1LdgxNSynzpd5Vyi3Ej12adEuWbo1.body:
> [kidcourageous](#comment_70_1aaGBN84Cc8VE7iocUxPXiRVhx9qSfXw6): No, again, my great grandpa literally was an SS officer who saw Auschwitz. Do not fucking take away my ancestors' accomplishments faggot. [...]

Did your grandpa talk about it much anon? I wanna hear some of his stories

1565241348_13CzgwZUSqr5FsFwgwjes7i6JY1Ts.body:
> [capitanjack](#comment_1_1DNJ1b7d7bqeZHigy35ZKBwwe8PBv8o7Gk): You probably mean removing users.json from zeronet/data folderHowever that way you will lose all of your certs unless u backup them somewhere

I've removed it and restarted ZeroNet, and it of course made a new users.json file. But on 08chan, for example, old posts I made are still recognized as *mine* "(You)", it shouldn't be doing this, should it?

> [anonkraut](#comment_6_1JpWZr3hPmL8cYSKQCzuqUyhG25UuQsjPh): If you have a real strong need for anonymity, your setup shouldn't have any permanent storage in the first place.

How would you go about setting up a dynamic storage?

> [capitanjack](#comment_2_1DNJ1b7d7bqeZHigy35ZKBwwe8PBv8o7Gk): try also removing millchan.db inside of 08chan folder (1DdPHedr5Tz55EtQWxqvsbEXPdc4uCVi9D)

Thanks! I think that worked

1566014746_17dcwh1uMFnDMZK8X5XHciXFggdxV.body:
I've been here for a month. The first 10 threads weren't fake, stop lying out of your ass. I remember first coming here and the community was very sincere and welcoming, it wasn't full of shill or clearly honeypot threads.

The new millchan engine has made browsing significantly faster, at least for me. Everything the admin has said thus far has been in line with 8ch's philosophy; the less moderation the better. This doesn't look like a fabricated honeypot to me (this doesn't mean we aren't still being watched though).
